==English==
===Etymology===
A contraction of [[pomegranate]], [[rhyming slang]] for [[immigrant]] ("imme-granate").

:''Many folk etymologies also exist:''
:*A devolution of "Prisoner of His/Her Majesty" or "POHM"
:*An acronym for "Prisoner of Mother England"

===Noun===
'''pom''' ([[poms]])

#(''Australian'', ''pejorative'') An [[Englishman]], A [[Briton]], A person of [[British]] decent.
#:'''Usage Note''': The use of this word to refer to a British person is considered by some to be pejorative. The word is, however, used by most Australians and some British people as a neutral or even affirmative term. It can however be considered offensive

